==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cacolet
<hw>Ca`co*let"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<def>A chair, litter, or other contrivance fitted to the back or pack
saddle of a mule for carrying travelers in mountainous districts, or for
the transportation of the sick and wounded of an army.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cacology</ent>⟦br⟧
